<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[Sat42]]></name></author>
<updated>2016-12-13T00:00:04+01:00</updated>
<published>2016-12-13T00:00:04+01:00</published>
<id>http://www.unrealsp.org/viewtopic.php?t=4121&amp;p=73503#p73503</id>
<link href="http://www.unrealsp.org/viewtopic.php?t=4121&amp;p=73503#p73503"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Map Of The Week • Re: 12/05/2016 - &quot;The Lands of Rostivelt&quot; by David Münnich]]></title>

<category term="Map Of The Week" scheme="http://www.unrealsp.org/viewforum.php?f=19" label="Map Of The Week"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.unrealsp.org/viewtopic.php?t=4121&amp;p=73503#p73503"><![CDATA[
<blockquote><div><cite>Semfry wrote:</cite><br />This is the most ONP-ass level in ONP. It looks good and has some impressive moments (although lots of it is ripped from DavidM's DM-Seed, which stuck out right away. Then again, I'm not sure on the timeline so it could have been partially concurrent?), but it's very linear, and most of the set-piece moments are more style than substance. Also, despite looking good, there's not really much of a sense of place beyond some generic Skaarj base; partially because of the linearity, but also because it adheres so dogmatically to ONP's cookie-cutter &quot;leet&quot; design style that it doesn't feel like it has anything distinguishing about it aesthetically. It does nothing notably bad and doesn't have any particular technical design flaws, but, in the end, it's just sort of there.<br /></div></blockquote><br /><br />Interesting comment. BTW I just checked the forum and saw that last time this was on MOTW, DavidM actually showed up!<br /><br />IMO, this is still - by the standards of <em>Unreal</em> - a great map, and it actually felt like it was slowly raising the level of the campaign back towards its earlier heights after two maps that - while fine in themselves (if really short and most definitely &quot;just there&quot;) - were quite a significant step down after the insane three-map suite that is <em>NP19</em> - in fact others have said that it would have made more sense to move directly from <em>Wipeout</em> to <em>The Lands of Rostivelt</em> (while keeping the awesome starting cave from <em>Entry to the Fire God Temple</em>, I'll add).<br /><br />I remember thinking the starting canyon had a cool design, yes (watching the video here, I admit I did not remember the Skaarj fighter and the Skaarj shuttle - the latter is unique to <em>ONP</em> - which make a brief appearance at the beginning of the map... it's cool to see that kind of thing but the campaign has shitloads of moments like that), and the Giant Manta fight was memorable despite being easy. BTW, the music section that plays when the Giant Manta attacks is awesome. I also recall being ambushed by a Skaarj that I mistakenly thought was dead <img class="smilies" src="http://www.unrealsp.org/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /> that's despite the trick being used more than once in this level. Good fights overall. <br /><br />Now a confession: of course, looking at the playthrough here it always seems everything is so easy, but man, on my first playthrough of this map I actually thought it was <em>hard</em>... essentially because of the last segment (although I have to say I did die once due to the Skaarj that jump down on you as you move out of the base): you see, back then I didn't realise I could destroy the turret <img class="smilies" src="http://www.unrealsp.org/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /> I definitely tried, but it didn't blow up with just a few shots so I assumed I had to make it across the lava zone under fire of the turret - making the passage very challenging with several reloads and that Skaarj showing up on the other side just added to my pain and eventually, I made it with literally a couple of hit points <img class="smilies" src="http://www.unrealsp.org/images/smilies/icon_surprised.gif" alt=":o" title="Surprised" /> and I was so nervous that after a quick save on the other side I also had to reload a couple of times due to the Skaarj with rocket launchers in the last big hall. <br />That sure was memorable, and IMO that makes <em>The Lands of Rostivelt</em> one of the hardest maps in <em>ONP</em>!<br /><br />There's also one stupid secret area... however the video just showed me there's another pretty legit secret area! <img class="smilies" src="http://www.unrealsp.org/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /><br /><br /><blockquote><div><cite>Doublez-Down wrote:</cite><br />Really enjoyed the scale and lighting in this map, and I remember it being fairly awe-inspiring at the time. [...] This (and some others from ONP) was one of those maps that made me realize I had SO MUCH to learn as a budding mapper that I just about gave it up - well I suppose I did for a while.<br /></div></blockquote><br /><br />I remember the first time I played <em>ONP</em> very well - a lot of the maps were much better looking than in the original <em>Unreal</em>/<em>UT</em>, and it felt like the engine had seen an upgrade! <br /><br /><blockquote><div><cite>Doublez-Down wrote:</cite><br />Wish I had more time to work on anything!<br /></div></blockquote><br /><br />Ditto <img class="smilies" src="http://www.unrealsp.org/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.unrealsp.org/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=623">Sat42</a> — 13 Dec 2016, 00:00</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
<entry>
